                    <heading>The Environment</heading>
                    <p id="BG.DIR.645">In order to comply with conditions for European Union membership, Bulgaria closed two of the Kozloduy nuclear power installation’s reactors at the end of 2002. A further two reactors were decommissioned in 2006. The Pirin National Park and the Srebarna Nature Reserve are World Heritage sites, in addition to the transboundary Ancient and Primeval Beech Forests. The Vratsa Karst Nature Reserve and the Central Balkan National Park are also important sites.</p>
